column2: Partly sunny with a slight breeze.
Calm- bright- algae on shore past few days.
Clear- calm- algae- heavy about 1 week ago.  Water level up.
Slightly cloudy- mod. breeze- some algae bloom near shore.
Partly cloudy- rain in A.M.- moderate winds.
Partly cloudy- calm- no significant algae bloom- June very turbulent.
Sunny- mild breeze- no surface findings.
Slight wind- many water skiers today.
Partly cloudy- calm- slight algae along rocks on shore.
Mild breeze- no bloom- partly cloudy.
First sunny- non-windy day this summer.
Partly sunny- storm the night before + wind.
Partly cloudy- no rain for 1 week.
Sunny- mild breeze- casual observation- not the usual clearness.
Partly sunny- slight breeze.  Last report for the season.
Clear blue sky- moderate west wind.
Sunny- but windy- this will be the last reading for this year- as we took our boat out.
Will be on vacation until July 1st then we resume the readings.
Sunny-calm wind.  I do realize this reading is 1' shallower I cannot understand why   Too much rain
Light wind today-but for the last 2 days had very high wind + whitecaps.
Calm-bright sun with a ripple wave.
Partly cloudy- light wind and waves.  Rained yesterday- most of the day.
High boat traffic yesterday-clear sun today-no wind.
Windy- bright sun.  Pair of loons w/ baby trying to teach it to dive.
Windy- bright sun-light boat traffic yesterday + today.
Partly cloudy- slight wind and waves.
Mostly sunny + calm.  No boat traffic.
Sunny-calm- no boat traffic yesterday or today.
Sunny and calm- no boat traffic.
Calm-bright sun with a ripple wake.
Strong winds- yesterday- light winds- today.
Clear and sunny skies.  Calm winds.
Bright sun- moderate wind.  Had rain last evening.
Sunny- but windy- no white caps.
Calm. 2 geese in bay on south end of lake. 2 loons also.
Slight waves.  Bright sun.  Partly cloudy.
Sunny.  Small waves.  Thunderstorm @ 3 AM + high wind.
Bright sun.  Dead calm.  No wind.
Bright sun and light wind.  Loons are back.
Bright sun and windy.  Pair of loons by Reed Island.
Bright sun.  Light wind and waves.
Bright sun and medium waves.  Saw pair of geese with 4 young on the lake.
Sunny and windy.  Geese still have 4 young ones.
Sunny.  Light wind.  Geese still have 4 young about the size of a good chicken.
Sunny and wavy from boat traffic.
Moderate waves and bright sun.  Partly cloudy.
Small waves.  Geese still have 4 young ones- almost full grown.
Small waves.  Bad storm and very heavy rain on 7/8/2000.
Moderate waves and partly sunny.  Heavy boat traffic.
Looks like there is a bloom in the water.
Bright Sun - Calm Water - No Wind
sunny and beautiful day-have been on vacation for a month in Montana
Bright sun and dead calm waters
Very high water due to the storms.
Nice day with some geese and ducks flying and swimming
Beautiful Calm and Sunny day for a change.
Lot of boat and jet ski traffic
Boats and water skiers busy over the week-end.
Bright sun- no boat traffic and calm waters
slight waves on the lake- beautiful day
clear sunny sky but a little bit windy.
Bright sunny day- and calm winds.
windy and wavy = clear sunny skies
Beautiful fall day. An eagle flew over as we were heading back to shore.
Windy day. Partly Cloudy. We have seen 4 loons this spring. The ice went out on the lake on 4/7/09.
Cloudy and 10-15 mph wind from the North
Slight breeze from the south- sunny
wind ese 3 mph  slight chop   sunny   4 adult loons- 2 baby loons
labor day weekend- moderate boat activity- 72-sunny- light wind 3-5 mph se- slight chop on water
Algae bloom - pine pollen in water- late spring- wet year- weed growth slow.
Sunny. Winds NW at 4-8 mph.- Sunny 82 degrees.
Partly cloudy. We had heavy rain the last 2 days.
Partly cloudy- high water. Southerly wind.
Mostly sunny- high water- wind from the south.
wind about 7 mph so a little choppy
slightly wavey but sunny  2 loons with 2 babies ready to leave for winter
surface temp 54 degrees F  13 feet 49 degrees F
